- This is a node based CLI tool called Weez.
- It's used for scaffolding frontend projects, one tool at at time. 
- It uses JavaScript for the CLI code.

Example:

```bash
weez prettier
```

At some future point, I may want to add an overall command that will install all tools, instead of one at a time.

- Here is the current directory structure:

weez-cli/
├── bin/
│   └── weez.js        # Entry point for the CLI (bin executable)
├── src/
│   ├── commands/      # Individual command implementations
│   │   ├── prettier.js
│   │   ├── eslint.js
│   │   └── index.js   # Exports all commands
│   ├── templates/     # Template files for configurations
│   │   ├── prettier/
│   │   │   └── .prettierrc.js
│   │   └── eslint/
│   │       └── eslint.config.mjs
│   ├── utils/         # Utility functions
│   │   ├── banner.js  # ASCII art and CLI banner
│   │   ├── file.js    # File operations
│   │   ├── npm.js     # npm/package.json operations
│   │   └── index.js   # Exports all utilities
│   └── index.js       # Main application logic
├── package.json
├── README.md
└── .gitignore


- Create conventional commit messages for changes.